<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>91554</id>
    <title>Calc adds empty style with new style from selection</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Tested on Windows XP SP3 and Windows 8 
Version: 5.0.0.0.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">beta1
Build ID: 0a16c3dda4150008d9be6f24cbd15ac198d116d3
Locale: es-MX (es_MX)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When try to create a new style from the new style from selection option, you can create a new style without name, then you can't delete it or change it.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Steps to reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">Create a new Calc File</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">Select the styles and formatting icon of the lateral toolbar</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">Select new style from selection icon</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">the create style windows displays</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.6">click OK without a name or typing anithing</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.7">an empty style is created</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Select the empty style and try to change it or delete it, but noting happens.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">If you add a new style from selecting the empty style, Calc hangs.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">If you give a name to another new style from default style selection, then you can change it or delete it, as expected.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Expected behavior: it should not accept a new style without a name, jus like in writer.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
